Description: Terra Sigillata wheel-made pottery sherd from a cup with a fine glossy red slip. Fine brown micaceous pottery fabric. Stamped inside.
Curator's comments: Imperial Roman red slip fine tableware sherd of Eastern Terra Sigillata B ware from Ephesus, cup form dated c. 1-70AD (Hayes 1985, form Atlal 70). Hayes, J. W. 1985. Sigillate Orientali. In Encicliopedia dell 'arte antica, atlante della forme ceramica. II ceramica fine Romana nel bacio Mediterraneo (Tardo ellenismo e primo imperio), pp. 1-96. Rome.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IF.080) (Phase 3)
